name: Population Sex Ratio, as of 1 July
Central death rate, nmx, for the age interval (x, x+n)
Probability of dying (nqx), for an individual between age x and x+n
Probability of surviving, (npx), for an individual of age x to age x+n
Number of survivors, (lx), at age (x) for 100000 births
Number of deaths, (ndx), between ages x and x+n
Number of person-years lived, (nLx), between ages x and x+n
Survival ratio (nSx) corresponding to proportion of the life table population in age group (x, x+n) who are alive n year later
Expectation of life (ex) at age x, i.e., average number of years lived subsequent to age x by those reaching age x
Average number of years lived (nax) between ages x and x+n by those dying in the interval
